            "body": "> Does it also happen with `cdef` syntax?\r\n\r\nWorks and runs fine:\r\n```\r\ncdef f():\r\n    def inner():  # should not be a cfunc\r\n        pass\r\n    return inner\r\n```\r\n\r\nFails correctly with \"C function definition not allowed here\"\r\n```\r\ncdef f():\r\n    cdef inner():  # should not be a cfunc\r\n        pass\r\n    return inner\r\n```\r\n\r\n------------------------------------------\r\n\r\nI can confirm `@cython.cclass` also has a very similar bug.",
